text: Milind Rege (16 February 1949 â€“ 19 February 2025) was an Indian first-class cricketer. He played for Bombay from 1967/68 to 1977/78. He was the chairman of selectors with the Mumbai Cricket Association. He had a heart attack on 19 February 2025, three days after his 76th birthday. He died the same day.
